- [P2] Verify ONNX assets before assigning pinned identity — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/0.8.16-slice-10-20260708T192441Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-embedder/src/ort_bge.rs:350-351
  When `from_files`/`from_env` is pointed at a different ONNX export or tokenizer revision, this still advertises the hard-coded pinned BGE identity. The engine relies on `EmbedderIdentity` to reject incompatible stored vectors, so an accidentally stale or alternate `FATHOMDB_ONNX_MODEL_PATH` can silently write/read vectors under the same identity even though the embedding space differs. Consider validating a pinned model/tokenizer digest or incorporating a checked asset revision into the identity before constructing it.
